# Project 01 – Windows Log Monitoring Deployment & Validation

## Objective

To deploy and configure Wazuh SIEM within a virtualised lab environment and validate successful ingestion and classification of Windows Security Event logs.

---

## Environment

- Wazuh SIEM (OVA deployment)
- Windows 10 endpoint
- VMware Workstation
- Isolated host-only network

---

## Deployment & Configuration

- Deployed Wazuh server using official OVA image.
- Installed and enrolled Windows agent using a pre-shared authentication key.
- Verified secure communication on port 1514.
- Resolved duplicate agent registration issue.
- Confirmed agent status transitioned to **Active**.

---

## Log Ingestion Validation

Approximately 800 Windows Security events successfully ingested.

Validated detection and parsing of:

- Event ID 4625 – Failed logon
- Event ID 7040 – Service configuration change

Confirmed rule classification and field extraction were functioning correctly.

---

## Outcome

The SIEM platform successfully ingested and classified Windows Security logs, establishing a functional monitoring baseline for further investigation scenarios.
